meters; the number of items; and the size of the defective set (or an upper\nbound on it). We also compare the bounds to information-theoretic lower bounds\nfor sample complexity based on Fano's inequality and show that the upper and\nlower bounds are equal up to an explicitly computable universal constant factor\n(independent of problem parameters).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2012 16:35:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2012 13:19:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2012 16:29:45 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 9 Sep 2012 03:28:12 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 5 Mar 2014 07:18:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-18"}
